OL,5, London Underground workers are set to  
OL,6, cast their vote on whether to take     
OL,7, strike action over pay.                
OL,9,FThe Rail, Maritime and Transport union 
OL,10,F(RMT) said it was unhappy at the latest
OL,11,Fpay offer from London Underground.     
OL,13,FIt also criticised the freezing of pay 
OL,14,Fbands, which it said would create a    
OL,15,Ftwo-tier workforce, and the creation of
OL,16,Fa #13m bonus pot for senior managers.  
OL,18,FTransport for London (TfL), which runs 
OL,19,FLondon Underground, has been approached
OL,20,Ffor comment.                           
